<dl id="n08073d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08073d">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08073d"> 73(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Irish gave up learning / speak I because E to<font color="green">[o]</font> / stupid to speak Irish</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">It sometimes happens in a district of mixed nationalities that the population which is intellectually superior give up their own language because they can learn their neighbours&apos; tongue while these are too dull to learn anything but their own. <small> Otto Jespersen, <a name="OJGS" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#OJGS"><cite title="source">The Growth and Structure of the English Language</cite></a>, 4th ed. (Jul 1923) 243</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
